Package com.pandora.config.services

package com.pandora.config.services
The com.pandora.config.services package provides services and interfaces related to the configuration and management of biogeochemical reactions and species in a freshwater context.

This package includes the following components:

  • .ReactionConfigurationBeanServiceImpl An interface defining methods for retrieving information about biogeochemical reaction configurations.
  • .ReactionConfigurationBeanServiceImpl: An implementation of ReactionConfigurationBeanService that utilizes the Spring framework's ApplicationContext to manage and retrieve instances of .ReactionConfiguration.
  • SpecieBeanService: An interface defining methods for retrieving information about biogeochemical species configurations.
  • SpecieBeanServiceImpl: An implementation of SpecieBeanService that uses the Spring framework's ApplicationContext to manage and retrieve instances of Specie.

Developers utilizing this package should refer to the documentation of individual classes and interfaces for detailed information on their purposes and methods.
